Connecting via Skype, Georgia Tech talked with Astronaut and Georgia Tech graduate Shane Kimbrough and his Japanese colleague Aki Hoshide at the International Space Station. 

During the inflight interview, Kimbrough and Hoshide talked about the energy around space exploration, the role of commanding the ISS, and plans to capture some pretty interesting images from the windows of the station.

Georgia Tech aerospace engineering student Anthony Limiero, built his own custom unicycle on campus and then rode it more than 300 miles from his parents' home in Tennessee back to  Atlanta. 

As president of Georgia Tech's unicycling club Limiero has also taught dozens of his classmates how to ride a unicycle.

node.title: Georgia Tech Student Builds Unicycle and Rides It 300 Miles Back To Campus

Made entirely of saplings and natural materials, the Chip Off the Old Block stickwork sculpture is at Georgia Tech as a reminder of the importance of nature and to build those positive associations with the environment.

Tech also served as the venue for swimming, diving, synchronized swimming, water polo, modern pentathlon, boxing, and Paralympic volleyball.
